    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 129.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatch of the 18th ultimo, No. 80, which is accompanied by a copy of a letter
                    from Mr. Hice, United States consul at Spezzia, published in Galignani’s
                    Messenger, in defence of Commodore Craven’s courage in the late affair with the
                    ram Stonewall off the port of Lisbon. Mr. Seward’s attention will be called to
                    the subject.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Biuelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
